Manual evidence snapshots for sources the fetch-evidence skill cannot reach
(closed-SaaS dashboards, air-gapped wikis, offline reports).

Layout: one subdirectory per source ID, e.g.
  .snapshots/grafana-prod-dashboard/panel-p99.png
  .snapshots/grafana-prod-dashboard/panel-p99.txt    (text excerpt for the agent)
  .snapshots/grafana-prod-dashboard/last_refreshed   (ISO 8601 timestamp, plain text)

The fetch-evidence skill (../../skills/fetch-evidence.md) checks this directory
when a source is otherwise unreachable and treats matching content as canonical.
If `last_refreshed` is older than the project's snapshot TTL (default 90 days),
the skill returns `staleness_warning: true` for that excerpt and the calling
agent's `uncertainty` rises accordingly.
